To construct a 'Datetime' value that is 3 weeks before the current date and time in Salesforce Apex, you can use the 'Datetime.now()' method combined with the 'addweeks' method. Here's how you can modify your code:

Datetime threeweeksago = Datetime.now().addweeks(-3);
LinkedSlots_Compute batch = new LinkedSlots_ComputeCellMetricsBatch();

This code will set the 'Datetime' value to 3 weeks before the current date and time. The 'addweeks(-3)' method subtracts 3 weeks from the current 'Datetime'.

Construct it to be 2024-05-28

To set the 'Datetime' value to 2024-05-28, you can use the 'Datetime.newInstance' method in Salesforce Apex. Here's how you can modify your code:

Datetime specificDate = Datetime.newInstance(2024, 5, 28, 0, 0, 0);
LinkedSlots_ComputeCellMetricsBatch batch = new LinkedSlots_ComputeCellMetricsBatch();

This code will set the 'Datetime' value to 2024-05-28 at midnight (00:00:00). If you need a different time of day, you can adjust the hours, minutes, and seconds accordingly.
